Citations
Date:  10/2/1921
Source:  Quick March
Author:
Vol / Page:  13
Edition:
Quote:  ... this reminiscence reminds me, too, of the variety of bush berries which we children would eat [in Carterton in the 1860s] - the white pine berries, the runi-runi, and ti-toke, these last very much resembling a raspberry, with a black seed on the head of it.
